JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress (ANC) in Ekurhuleni is calling on the city to oppose what it calls the Democratic Alliances's (DA) frivolous and desperate attempt to abuse the courts, after the DA was granted an urgent interdict against a special council sitting. READ: Ekurhuleni Council Chief Whip Khetha Shandu resigns City Manager Imogen Mashazi scheduled the sitting to take place last Monday after seven minority parties filed a motion of no confidence against Council Speaker Raymond Dhlamini. However, the sitting could not take place, after the Johannesburg High Court approved the party and Dhlamini's application to prevent the sitting from taking place. This means he will continue his duties as speaker. READ: Zille: ActionSA trying to bring DA in Ekurhuleni down 'speaks for itself'